      "role": "user",
      "content": "\"overwhelming evidence\"? that seems like a huge claim. isn't it pretty controversial among historians? some people say the more radical groups were actually what forced the government's hand because they were scared of what would happen if they didn't negotiate with MLK. doesn't it feel a bit one-sided to say nonviolence was definitively the most effective?",
